$ Stellarium Script API

Some selected functions from the → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium script API.

{ ConstellationMgr

  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/ConstellationMgr/setFlagLines[`setFlagLines`] displays the lines between the constallations' stars
}
{ core

  table { ll
  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/clear[`clear`] ☰ clears display options for a «standard view» (such as natural, starchart, deepspace, galactic).
  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/debug[`debug`] ☰ writes text to the → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/console/index[ScriptConsole] output window
  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/getDate[`getDate`] ☰ returns the current simulation time in → misc/ISO/8601[ISO 8601] format
  `getObjectInfo` ☰ gets information about an object in the sky, see the dialog → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/GUI/popups/Configuration/Information[Configuration -> Information]
  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/getObjectPosition[`getObjectPosition`] ☰ gets (postional) information about an object in the sky.
  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/getScreenWidth_Height[`getScreenWidth_Height`] ☰ 
  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/moveToAltAzi[`moveToAltAzi`] ☰ look at a pair of coordinates that are specified in the *horizontal coordinate system*.
  `moveToObject()` ☰ look at a given object
  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/moveToRaDec[`moveToRaDec`] ☰ 
  `moveToSelectedObject()` ☰ look at selected object
  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/pauseScript[`pauseScript`] ☰ 
  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/screenshot[`screenshot`] ☰ Make a screenshot from the scene
  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/selectObjectByName[`selectObjectByName`] ☰ 
  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/setDate[`setDate`] ☰ go to a specific point in time. Can be specified absolutely (→ misc/ISO/8601[ISO 8601]) or relatively `"+ 4 days"`.
  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/setDeltaTAlgorithm[`setDeltaTAlgorithm`] ☰ 
  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/setGuiVisible[`setGuiVisible`] ☰ Toggles visiblity of (GUI-)toolbars that provide the public slot `setGuiVisible()`.
  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/setMilkyWayIntensity[`setMilkyWayIntensity`] ☰ 
  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/setMilkyWayVisible[`setMilkyWayVisible`] ☰ 
  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/setSelectedObjectInfo[`setSelectedObjectInfo`] ☰ controls the amount of information that is shown when an object is select.
  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/setObserverLocation[`setObserverLocation`] ☰ travels to a given location on Earth or a planet.
  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/setTimeRate[`setTimeRate`] ☰ 
  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/wait[`wait`] ☰ Stop the presentation for a given period
  table }

}
